When you die, you appear in a cinema with a number of other people who look like you. You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching your next life on the big screen.

"This can't be happening to me", I thought to myself.  "Am I still alive?  Is this all one big dream?  The last thing that I remember is going to bed next to my wife".  Someone who looked like an 18 -year old version of me walked up to where I was sitting.   He told me that he knew how it felt when he first got here.  He was scared.  "You get used to it, though", he said.    "How long have you been here?", I asked.  "FDR was president when I died", he replied.

"Wow.  So, we just sit here and watch how our future selves live their life?", I whispered to him.   "Yep.  This is an endless cycle.  I am not sure what will happen when more of us get into the cinema.  There are only so many seats in here.  Maybe, we will get a nice theater upgrade down the road", he said.

"This can't be happening to me", I thought to myself.  "Am I still alive?  Is this all one big dream?  The last thing that I remember is going to bed next to my wife".  Someone who looked like an 18 -year old version of me walked up to where I was sitting.   He told me that he knew how it felt when he first got here.  He was scared.  "You get used to it, though", he said.    "How long have you been here?", I asked.  "FDR was president when I died", he replied.

"Wow.  So, we just sit here and watch how our future selves live their life?", I whispered to him.   "Yep.  This is an endless cycle.  I am not sure what will happen when more of us get into the cinema.  There are only so many seats in here.  Maybe, we will get a nice theater upgrade down the road", he said.

"You get used to it, though", he said.    "How long have you been here?", I asked.  "FDR was president when I died", he replied.

"Wow.  So, we just sit here and watch how our future selves live their life?", I whispered to him.   "Yep.  This is an endless cycle. Someone who looked like an 18 -year old version of me walked up to where I was sitting.   He told me that he knew how it felt when he first got here.  He was scared.  "You get used to it, though", he said.    "How long have you been here?", I asked.  "FDR was president when I died", he replied.

"Wow.  So, we just sit here and watch how our future selves live their life?", I whispered to him.   "Yep.  This is an endless cycle.  I am not sure what will happen when more of us get into the cinema.  There are only so many seats in here.  Maybe, we will get a nice theater upgrade down the road", he said.

Someone who looked like an 18 -year old version of me walked up to where I was sitting.   He told me that he knew how it felt when he first got here.  He was scared.  "You get used to it, though", he said.    "How long have you been here?", I asked.  "FDR was president when I died", he replied.

"Wow.  So, we just sit here and watch how our future selves live their life?", I whispered to him.   "Yep.  This is an endless cycle.  I am not sure what will happen when more of us get into the cinema.  There are only so many seats in here.  Maybe, we will get a nice theater upgrade down the road", he said.
